<br>
So, my question to you guys is: think they give you a means of reducing aggro? Or will that forever be a downside to choosing the Mage class? <br>
<br>
One last question on the same subject. How much do you find yourself limited by aggro on raids? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhionsligo>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1267<br> <font color=#333333>(1/2/03 3:20:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages and aggro</span><hr size=1> The reason mages don't have a large problem with this is:<br>
<br>
Every class seemingly has an aggro modifier.  Of all the spellcasters, magicians have one of the lowest values as their aggro modifier.  This means that you can do more damage than a druid can before you become the focus of a NPC.<br>
<br>
I have tested this, and you can too. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=106710"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
My Character Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rabidsheep>rabidsheep</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#333333>(1/2/03 10:45:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages and aggro</span><hr size=1> and another thing, (mostly works pre60 with epic) if you have more aggro then the tank, but your pet has more aggro then the tank as well, the pet keeps the mob in place while the tank keeps aggro due to the fact that no pet can take aggro over a PC<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  thats cool<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227830">Rabids Arch Convoker</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tukodo>Tukodo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 188<br> <font color=#333333>(1/2/03 11:17:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages and aggro</span><hr size=1> The topic still gets avoided.  I brought this up awhile ago and a lot of inexperienced mages in raid settings seem to think we don't need one.<br>
<br>
I can still get summoned from nuking with a warrior duel weilding enraging blow weapons (rarely but it happens).  It would just be nice to have some sort of agro reducing spell when this happens to avoid death or pulling the mob out of placement.<br>
<br>
I don't see why it is such a big deal that we have a way to lower agro when most classes designed to do damage have one already.  Not like this would totally unbalance the class or anything.<br>
<br>
<br>
Tukodo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhionsligo>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1269<br> <font color=#333333>(1/3/03 4:09:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages and aggro</span><hr size=1> Enabling a class to significantly raise its dps...IS powerful.<br>
<br>
Overpowering?  Well that's tough to know since I don't know what an acceptable dps for our class with a warrior holding aggro should be. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=106710"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
My Character Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zyphyr>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 768<br> <font color=#333333>(1/3/03 6:42:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages and aggro</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I brought this up awhile ago and a lot of inexperienced mages in raid settings seem to think we don't need one.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A lot of mages who <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>are</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> experienced in raiding think we don't need one too.<br>
<br>
<br>
Sure, we can get summoned if we go all-out. But then, so can Wizards, Necros, Rangers, etc (even if they are using their agro-reducing abilities). <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44185">Vending Machine, Disciple of Zomm, and husband to Sarrena Destini</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
